http://batyrchary2001527.herokuapp.com/

Comments:
	I used django,python for implementation.
	Letters, 1+1 kind of inputs and numbers which have more than 10 digits are not valid inputs. 

Usage:
1. Extract all files to some folder. Lets call it "deneme"
2. cd deneme
3. inside deneme 
	$ pip install virtualenv		// if you have already installed it skip this part	
	$ virtualenv venv			//for ubuntu, for windows use $venv\Scripts\activate
	$ source venv/bin/activate	
	$ pip install -r requirements.txt
	
4. if all installation completed without errors, now you should be able to try it locally, by executing "$ heroku local web"

5. And you should be able to deploy it by executing this commands:
	$ git add .
	$ git commit -m "message."
	$ heroku login
		Enter your Heroku credentials.
		...
	$heroku create
	$git push heroku master
